<P>
"The Wonder Years" is so painfully realistic that I'm certain its writers were 
once junior high school students! I've been out of junior high school for 23 
years now, but with each new episode, I feel myself reliving those awkward, 
frustrating years. The show is terrific, but let's tone down the realism. I get 
enough stress watching "thirtysomething." 
</P>
<P>
Henry Sakaida, Temple City 
</P>
</TEXT>
