<TEXT>
<P>
"The reality is that there is a lot of merchandise on the floors of the stores, 
and if you want to get people to buy it now, you've got to lower prices." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Irving J. Weintraub, Los Angeles director of retail services at Deloitte 
&amp; Touche, on the outlook for retailers on the final weekend of shopping 
before Christmas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA122489-0028 </DOCNO>
