<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANIMAL ACTIVISTS ARE CRITICIZED FOR IGNORING CONSTITUTIONAL AND ENVIRONMENTAL 
REALITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding the article about animal furs, I agree that furs should not be 
obtained from endangered animals or through the use of inhumane traps, but 
animals raised for their fur are the same to me as animals raised for their 
meat. 
</P>
<P>
If an activist leads an existence free of animal byproducts obtainable only 
through the animal's death, then and only then would I respect his opinion. 
</P>
<P>
STAR MEYER 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
