<HEADLINE>
<P>
WATER HEATER SAFETY STRAPS, INSULATION OFFERED TO SENIORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PICO RIVERA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city is expanding its Paint-Up and Fix-Up Program, a special service for 
low-income senior citizens and handicapped homeowners. 
</P>
<P>
According to Mayor John Chavez, qualified residents can have insulation 
blankets and earthquake safety straps installed on their water heaters free of 
charge. 
</P>
<P>
City officials estimate that by wrapping a water heater with an insulated 
blanket, residents can save about 20% on their water-heating bills. A strap can 
keep the water heater from tipping over in an earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
The Paint-Up and Fix-Up Program also includes installation of smoke detectors 
and deadbolt locks, repair of broken windows and repainting of home exteriors. 
The services are free. Eligible homeowners may contact the Pico Rivera Housing 
Department at 942-2000, Ext. 276. 
</P>
</TEXT>
