<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLITICS OF ABORTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Recently there has been a rash of abandoned babies in the Southland, who have 
been left in trash bins or on doorsteps. Instead of being chastised, women who 
do this should be treated with empathy and compassion, as they are often young 
girls who are scared, desperate and without any family support. How can we 
bring hundreds of thousands of additional children into the world, which is 
what anti-abortionists advocate, when we can't even properly care for those we 
already have? 
</P>
<P>
KENNETH L. ZIMMERMAN 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 
</P>
