<P>
DRIVING IN THE CAR-POOL LANE WITH CHILDREN AS PASSENGERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to letters by R.F. Craig and Andrea Kinney about children as 
passengers in car-pool lanes (Dec. 17): 
</P>
<P>
I disagree with their contention that I am not taking another adult driver off 
the freeway when I have only children in my car. 
</P>
<P>
I am in fact taking two adult drivers off the freeway by car-pooling my 
children and theirs to school. 
</P>
<P>
I hope that the next time they see someone with children in the car-pool lane 
they will think that just maybe that person is keeping an adult off the freeway 
by taking their children someplace they both might have driven to. 
</P>
<P>
MELINDA DAVIS 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 
