TRUST FUND SET FOR INJURED TORRANCE HIGH FOOTBALL PLAYER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A trust fund has been established for Torrance High football player Jason 
Knight, who was paralyzed in a game this season. Knight, a sophomore, is 
undergoing rehabilitation at Rancho Los Amigos Hospital in Downey. 
</P>
<P>
Contributions may be mailed to the Jason Knight Trust Fund, Torrance National 
Bank, PO Box 4199, Torrance 90505. For information, contact Torrance High 
sophomore Coach Bill Bynum, 539-5320 or 334-4111. 
</P>
<P>
Gardena will hold a basketball officials training clinic Jan. 10 and 16. 
Participants will be eligible to officiate city league games for $10 a game. 
For more information call 217-9537 or 217-9598. 
</P>
<P>
Boys and girls ages 6-12 can enroll in the annual YMCA Youth Basketball League 
to be played at the Gardena/Carson branch each Saturday beginning Jan. 6. 
Volunteer coaches are needed. Call 327-0750. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA's defending national champion women's softball team will conduct a clinic 
Jan. 27 from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. at the Bruin intramural field. Team enrollment, 
at $15 per player, is encouraged. Individuals pay $20 if enrolled early or $25 
at the door. For more information call Sue Enquist at 399-0872 or the UCLA 
athletic department at 206-6779. 
</P>
<P>
Hawthorne is forming teams at city park offices for winter youth basketball. 
Youths in fourth, fifth and sixth grades are eligible. The cost is $5 per 
athlete. Call 970-7230. 
</P>
