<P>
DEFENSE CARRIES CHANNEL ISLANDS TO EASY VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRBY LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Channel Islands used an aggressive, full-court defense to coast to a 55-27 win 
over Rio Mesa on Saturday in the second round of the Thousand Oaks girls' 
basketball tournament at Thousand Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
Candis Carper scored 14 points to lead four Channel Islands players in double 
figures. Carrie Davidson, Camisca Hawkins and Sal Pauau each scored 10 points. 
</P>
<P>
Rio Mesa (3-4) scored its first field goal with 6:23 left in the first half, 
making the score 16-4. 
</P>
<P>
Channel Islands (6-3) scored 12 unanswered points to open the third quarter 
before Eryn Farney hit a 20-foot jump shot. 
</P>
<P>
In other tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
Palmdale 51, Hueneme 36 -- Karee Bonde scored a game-high 21 points to lead the 
Falcons to a second-round win. Bonde, held without a point in the third 
quarter, scored seven in the final period. 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks 40, Burroughs (Ridgecrest) 35 -- Michele Palmisano scored a 
game-high 31 points for Thousand Oaks (6-4). The Lancers raced to a 16-4 
first-quarter lead, but Burroughs battled back to trail at the half, 21-16. 
KIRBY LEE 
</P>
