</P>
<P>
The Thousand Island of the '80s. 
</P>
<P>
Haute Southwest Cuisine: 
</P>
<P>
Born not on a wind-swept Arizona mesa but in a Manhattan Beach shopping mall. 
</P>
<P>
Eating It Raw: 
</P>
<P>
Once carpaccio was a specific Italian term denoting thinly sliced raw beef, 
usually drizzled with olive oil. But in the '80s we ate carpaccio of 
tuna/salmon/sea bass (once known simply as sashimi), carpaccio of vegetables 
(once known as crudites) carpaccio of mushrooms (once known as mushrooms). 
</P>
<P>
