</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 2; Column 2; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
249 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLIDAY CLOSINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Monday is Christmas Day, and Jan. 1 is New Year's Day. The following will be 
closed in observance of the holidays: 
</P>
<P>
All county, state and federal offices. 
</P>
<P>
Schools, including colleges and universities. Public elementary, junior and 
high schools will reopen Jan. 2. 
</P>
<P>
County, state and federal courthouses. 
</P>
<P>
City and county libraries. 
</P>
<P>
Banks and savings and loans. 
</P>
<P>
City offices will be closed only on Christmas and New Year's days with the 
following exceptions: Fullerton offices will be closed Monday through Jan. 1; 
those of Buena Park, Cypress, Garden Grove, La Palma, San Juan Capistrano and 
Stanton will be closed Monday and Tuesday and Jan. 1 and 2. 
</P>
<P>
Mail: All post offices will be closed Christmas and New Year's days, and mail 
deposited in mailboxes on those days will be picked up according to the posted 
holiday schedule. 
</P>
<P>
Trash: There will be no trash pickup by city or county refuse workers Christmas 
or New Year's days. Trash pickups will be a day late for the rest of the week 
for both weeks. 
</P>
<P>
Buses: Orange County Transit District buses will run on the holiday schedule 
Christmas and New Year's days. Call the district at (714) 636-7433 for 
information. The bus routes that will be running are 29, 41, 43, 44, 47, 49, 
50, 51, 53, 54, 55, 57, 60, 64, 66, 69, 70 and 85. There will be no dial-a-ride 
or car-pool services available on the holidays. 
</P>
<P>
Parks: All city- and county-run parks and recreation facilities will be open 
during regular hours Christmas and New Year's days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
